messages.message:
Hi Team, I encountered this error when performing a smoketest for SwissRe. When I click "Publish" I get an error stating the sample results could not be generated. However if I navigate away and return, it's already published. So from a user standpoint there's no blocker but I wanted to share in case this is an unknown bug.
cc @Kim Acevedo
CC: @Elan Sharony @Jag also tagging @Abhishek Adupa (feel free to re-tag) on the license issue here
hmm i remember @Victor Zeng and @Sayan discussing this bug in the office yesterday?

Could you also send which environment this is in? Was trying this in UAT yesterday and saw this bug. In addition, after we assigned the license to the *username* we were able to see the publishing succeeded. I believe it took longer in this case as well since the sample results may have actually been generated.
@Sayan this was for https://swissre.aihub.instabase.com/, I was logged in as <mailto:admin@instabase.com|admin@instabase.com>
